OL,3,CTeenage girls are less likely to feel
OL,4,Csafe in school than boys, study finds
OL,6,FTeenage girls in England are
OL,7,Fsignificantly less likely to feel safe
OL,8,Fin school than their male classmates
OL,9,Fsince the Covid pandemic, a study has
OL,10,Fsuggested.
OL,12,FResearchers from University College
OL,13,FLondon measured engagement indicators
OL,14,Fincluding: liking school, feeling
OL,15,Fsafe, belonging, a sense of care from
OL,16,Fteachers and pride in their school.
OL,18,FThe data was then compared with 32
OL,19,Fother participating countries for
OL,20,Fanalysis.
