OL,3,CTeenage girls are less likely to feel
OL,4,Csafe in school than boys, study finds
OL,6,FIt also found that girls in Year 9 in
OL,7,Fparticipating countries reported
OL,8,Ffeeling significantly less safe in
OL,9,F2023 than in 2019, with England seeing
OL,10,Fone of the biggest drop-offs.
OL,12,FOverall, Year 9 pupils in England in
OL,13,F2023 had some of the lowest levels of
OL,14,Fschool belonging among the countries
OL,15,Fanalysed for the study.
OL,17,FThe researchers concluded that pupils'
OL,18,Fdeclining emotional engagement with
OL,19,Fschool was likely to be a "key driver"
OL,20,Fof pupil absences.
