OL,3,CTeenage girls are less likely to feel
OL,4,Csafe in school than boys, study finds
OL,6,FProfessor John Jerrim, the lead author
OL,7,Fof the study at UCL's Faculty of
OL,8,FEducation and Society, said: "The
OL,9,Fresults we are seeing for girls are
OL,10,Fparticularly concerning, with around a
OL,11,Fthird of teenage girls in this country
OL,12,Findicating they no longer feel safe at
OL,13,Fschool."
OL,15,FHe added: "Our research points towards
OL,16,Fsomething happening during the
OL,17,Fpandemic - quite possibly school
OL,18,Fclosures - that has particularly
OL,19,Fimpacted teenage girls.
